## Billing address

The following HTTP GET request:

<pre class="terminal">
https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

returns the user's billing address in [JSON](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSON)
format:

<pre class="terminal">
$ curl https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name": "Τάσος",
  "last_name": "Τασάκης",
  "email": "home@example.com",
  "mobile": "6971234567",
  "phone": "2101234567",
  "address": "Πάρου 34",
  "zip": "17234",
  "city": "Αθήνα",
  "region": "Αττικής",
  "street_name": "Πάρου",
  "street_number": "34",
  "invoice": false,
  "company": "",
  "doy": "",
  "afm": "",
  "profession": "",
  "company_phone": ""
}
~~~

Τhe `Address` resource supports [JSONP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSONP).

Once you complete the required server-side OAuth steps, you can expose the `oauth_token` at
the client (browser) side.  
Then, by using JavaScript and an [XHR](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XMLHttpRequest)
you can retrieve the user address and pre-fill the form.

To get the billing address of a user in [JSONP](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSONP)
format, you have to set the `callback` parameter with the function name (e.g. `aFunction`)
you want to be invoked.

<pre class="terminal">
$ curl https://www.<%= settings.domain %>/oauth2/address?callback=aFunction&oauth_token=124fFAGRNJru1FTz70BzhT3Zg...
</pre>

~~~ javascript
aFunction({
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com"
    ...
})
~~~

## Shipping address

In case the shipping address is different from the billing address, the `shipping_address`
field will be present along with all shipping information. For example:

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com",
  "mobile":"6971234567",
  "phone":"2101234567",
  "address":"Πάρου 34",
  "zip":"17234",
  "city":"Αθήνα",
  "region":"Αττικής",
  "street_name":"Πάρου",
  "street_number":"34",
  "invoice":false,
  "company":"",
  "doy":"",
  "afm":"",
  "profession":"",
  "company_phone":"",
  "shipping_address":{
    "first_name":"Τάσος",
    "last_name":"Τασάκης",
    "mobile":"",
    "phone":"2101234567",
    "address":"Σύρου 12",
    "zip":"18151",
    "city":"Αθήνα",
    "region":"Αττικής"
    "street_name":"Σύρου",
    "street_number":"12"
  }
}
~~~

## Invoice

If the user requested an invoice, then `invoice` will be `true` and the
relevant fields (`company`, `doy`, `afm`, `profession`, `company_phone`) will
be filled with the information.

~~~ javascript
{
  "first_name":"Τάσος",
  "last_name":"Τασάκης",
  "email":"home@example.com",
  "mobile":"6971234567",
  "phone":"2101234567",
  "address":"Πάρου 34",
  "zip":"17234",
  "city":"Αθήνα",
  "region":"Αττικής",
  "street_name":"Πάρου",
  "street_number":"34",
  "invoice":true,
  "company":"Skroutz",
  "doy":"Α Αθηνων",
  "afm":"123456789",
  "profession":"Engineer",
  "company_phone":"2101234567"
}
~~~

